	var req = request.body.data.request;
	var ses = request.body.data.session;

	var ER = new EchoRequest(ses, req);
	ER.process();
	
	response.setStatus(200);
	response.setContentType("application/json;charset=UTF-8");
	var writer = response.getStreamWriter();

	writer.writeString(global.JSON.stringify(ER.response));	

	return;

})(request, response);

sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_metadata_link"><sys_metadata_link action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><directory>update</directory><documentkey>0555b24edb5db200d1a9f1351d961952</documentkey><payload><?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<record_update table="x_snc_amazon_echo_intent">
    <x_snc_amazon_echo_intent action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE">
        <active>false</active>
        <always_available>false</always_available>
        <category/>
        <fallback>false</fallback>
        <intent_ends_session>false</intent_ends_session>
        <keyword>CreateIncident</keyword>
        <name>Create an Incident (Create)</name>
        <next_intent/>
        <order/>
        <output_speech_format/>
        <reprompt_speech_format/>
        <script><![CDATA[(function(content, attributes, erb){
	var issueText = content.Description.value;
	var userName = attributes.UserAttributes.name;
	
	var inc = new GlideRecord('incident');
	inc.initialize();
	inc.short_description = issueText;
	inc.description = "Opened by: " + userName + "\n" + issueText;
	inc.contact_type = "Alexa";
	var id = inc.insert();
	
	var incRec = new GlideRecord('incident');
	incRec.get(id);
	var number = incRec.number;
	
	var num = number.toString();
	var numS = num.slice(-7);
	
	var incNum = "<say-as interpret-as='spell-out'>" + "INC" + "</say-as> <say-as interpret-as='digits'>" + numS + "</say-as>";
	
	var ssml = "<speak>";
	ssml += "Your incident has been created. Here is your confirmation number: " + incNum;
	//ssml += "<say-as interpret-as='digits'>" + number +"</say-as>.";
	ssml += "</speak>";
	
	erb.setOutputSpeech("SSML", null, ssml);
	//erb.setReprompt("PlainText", "I didn't catch that. Tell me your issue by saying 'My issue is...' followed by your issue.", "");
	erb.setEnd(true);
	result = erb.response;
})(content, attributes, new EchoResponseBuilder());]]></script>
        <slot_name_1>Description</slot_name_1>
        <slot_name_2/>
        <slot_name_3/>
        <slot_type_1 display_value="AMAZON.LITERAL">d480c646dbd9b200d1a9f1351d9619a6</slot_type_1>
        <slot_type_2/>
        <slot_type_3/>

        <sys_mod_count>3</sys_mod_count>
        <sys_updated_by>jc</sys_updated_by>
        <sys_updated_on>2017-04-13 02:02:30</sys_updated_on>
        <top_level_intent>false</top_level_intent>
    </x_snc_amazon_echo_intent>
</record_update>

sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>package_private</access><active>true</active><api_name>x_snc_amazon_echo.EchoLog</api_name><client_callable>false</client_callable><description/><name>EchoLog</name><script><![CDATA[var EchoLog = Class.create();
EchoLog.prototype = {
	initialize: function(session, request, response) {
		this.session = session;
		this.request = request;
		this.response = response;
		this.sessionRec = this.getSession(this.session);
		this.intent = this.getIntent(this.request.intent.name);
	},

	log : function() {
		//Create two log entries. One for request and one for response. Each call to this class will have both.
		var log = new GlideRecord('x_snc_amazon_echo_log');
		//Log request
		log.initialize();
		log.type = 'Inbound';
		log.intent = this.intent.record.sys_id;
		log.spoken_phrase = this.intent.returnPhrase;
		log.session = this.sessionRec.sys_id;
		log.content = JSON.stringify(this.request, null, 4);
		var newRequest = log.insert();

		//Log response
		log.initialize();
		log.type = 'Outbound';
		log.session = this.sessionRec.sys_id;
		log.spoken_phrase = this.getResponsePhrase(this.response.response.outputSpeech);
		log.content = JSON.stringify(this.response, null, 4);
		log.ends_session = this.response.response.shouldEndSession;
		log.in_response_to = newRequest;
		log.insert();		
		return;
	},
	
	getSession : function(s) {
		//Get session record if exists. Create if it doesn't. Returns session GlideRecord
		var sid = s.sessionId.substr(s.sessionId.indexOf(".") + 1);

		var session = new GlideRecord('x_snc_amazon_echo_session');
		if (session.get('session_id', sid))
			return session;
		else {
			session.initialize();
			session.session_id = sid;
			var sessionRec = session.insert();
			session.get(sessionRec);
			return session;
		}
	},

	getIntent : function(intent) {
		var iObj = {};
		
		var i = new GlideRecord('x_snc_amazon_echo_intent');
		if (i.get('keyword', intent)) {
			iObj.record = i;
			
			//Get primary phrase and log it
			var phrase = new GlideRecord('x_snc_amazon_echo_phrases');
			phrase.addQuery('intent', i.sys_id);
			phrase.addQuery('primary', 'true');
			phrase.query();
			
			if (phrase.next())
				iObj.returnPhrase = phrase.phrase + '';
			else
				iObj.returnPhrase = i.name + '';
			
			return iObj;
		}

		gs.info("EchoLog: Unable to resolve intent and attach to log.");
		return;
	},
	
	getResponsePhrase : function(speech) {
		var type = speech.type;
		var text = speech.text;
		var ssml = speech.ssml;
		
		if (type == 'PlainText')
			return text;
		else if (type == 'SSML') 
			return ssml.replace(/<(?:.|\n)*?>/gm, '');
		else
			return 'Whoops! Unable to parse response speech. :(';
	},

	type: 'EchoLog'
};]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_include</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>jc</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2017-03-13 22:19:11</sys_created_on><sys_customer_update>true</sys_customer_update><sys_id>b248b2a8db61f600d1a9f1351d9619bb</sys_id><sys_mod_count>32</sys_mod_count><sys_name>EchoLog</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Amazon Echo" source="x_snc_amazon_echo">101eb7da13a21200d0143d622244b063</sys_package><sys_policy>read</sys_policy><sys_replace_on_upgrade>false</sys_replace_on_upgrade><sys_scope display_value="Amazon Echo">101eb7da13a21200d0143d622244b063</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_include_b248b2a8db61f600d1a9f1351d9619bb</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>jc</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2017-03-17 04:46:34</sys_updated_on></sys_script_include></record_update>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update sys_domain="global" table="sys_script"><sys_script action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><abort_action>false</abort_action><access>package_private</access><action_delete>false</action_delete><action_insert>true</action_insert><action_query>false</action_query><action_update>true</action_update><active>true</active><add_message>false</add_message><advanced>true</advanced><change_fields>false</change_fields><client_callable>false</client_callable><collection>x_snc_amazon_echo_intent</collection><condition/><description/><execute_function>false</execute_function><filter_condition table="x_snc_amazon_echo_intent">fallbackCHANGESTOtrue^EQ<item endquery="false" field="fallback" goto="false" newquery="false" operator="CHANGESTO" or="false" value="true"/><item endquery="true" field="" goto="false" newquery="false" operator="=" or="false" value=""/></filter_condition><is_rest>false</is_rest><message/><name>Only one top-level intent allowed</name><order>100</order><priority>100</priority><rest_method/><rest_method_text/><rest_service/><rest_service_text/><rest_variables/><role_conditions/><script><![CDATA[(function executeRule(current, previous /*null when async*/) {

	var gr = new GlideRecord(current.getTableName());
	gr.addQuery('fallback', 'true');
	gr.addQuery('sys_id', '!=', current.sys_id);
	gr.query();

	if (gr.next()){
		current.setAbortAction(true);
		var error = 'Only one Intent can be set up as a Fallback. ' + gr.name + ' is the current Fallback.';
		current.fallback.setError(error);
	}

})(current, previous);]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>jc</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2017-04-13 01:59:30</sys_created_on><sys_customer_update>true</sys_customer_update><sys_domain>global</sys_domain><sys_domain_path>/</sys_domain_path><sys_id>7a39ca96db0af600d1a9f1351d961928</sys_id><sys_mod_count>1</sys_mod_count><sys_name>Only one top-level intent allowed</sys_name><sys_overrides/><sys_package display_value="Amazon Echo" source="x_snc_amazon_echo">101eb7da13a21200d0143d622244b063</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_replace_on_upgrade>false</sys_replace_on_upgrade><sys_scope display_value="Amazon Echo">101eb7da13a21200d0143d622244b063</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_7a39ca96db0af600d1a9f1351d961928</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>jc</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2017-04-13 02:02:18</sys_updated_on><template/><when>before</when></sys_script><sys_translated_text action="delete_multiple" query="documentkey=7a39ca96db0af600d1a9f1351d961928"/></record_update>

<record_update table="x_snc_amazon_echo_intent">
    <x_snc_amazon_echo_intent action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE">
        <active>true</active>
        <always_available>false</always_available>
        <category/>
        <fallback>false</fallback>
        <intent_ends_session>false</intent_ends_session>
        <keyword>ServiceInterruptions</keyword>
        <name>Are there any service interruptions?</name>
        <next_intent/>
        <order>300</order>
        <output_speech_format>PlainText</output_speech_format>
        <reprompt_speech_format/>
        <script><![CDATA[(function(current, content, attributes, ER, IntentUtils){
	
	var msg = "";
	
	var gr = new GlideRecord('cmdb_ci_outage');
	gr.addEncodedQuery('begin<=javascript:gs.daysAgoEnd(0)^endISEMPTY');
	gr.query();
	
	while (gr.next()){
		msg += "There is " + (gr.type == 'outage' ? "an " : "a ") + gr.type.getDisplayValue() + ' affecting the ' + gr.cmdb_ci.getDisplayValue()  + " " +  gr.cmdb_ci.sys_class_name.getDisplayValue() + ". ";
	}
	
	
	ER.setOutputSpeech(current.output_speech_format, msg);
	//ER.setReprompt("PlainText/SSML", "Text goes here", "SSML goes here");
	//ER.setAttributes(attrObj); = Object of session attributes
	ER.setEnd(current.intent_ends_session);

	result = ER.response; //Required
})(current, content, attributes, new EchoResponseBuilder(), new IntentUtils());]]></script>

        <slot_name_2/>
        <slot_name_3/>
        <slot_type_1/>
        <slot_type_2/>
        <slot_type_3/>

        <top_level_intent>true</top_level_intent>
    </x_snc_amazon_echo_intent>
</record_update>

sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sp_css"><sp_css action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><css>.echo-top-content {
  color: #fff; 
}

.content-box {
  background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.23);
  margin: 10px;
  width: 90%;
  height: 460px;
  color: #fff;
}

.instructions {
  font-size: large;
}

.header {
  text-align: center;
  font-size: xx-large;
  padding-bottom: 10px;
}

.subheader {
  text-align: center;
  padding: 20px;
}

.intent {
  width: 100%;
  height: 128px;
}

.icon-row {
  padding-top: 10px;
  padding-bottom: 10px;
}

.icon-box {
  height: 42px;
  display: inline-block;
  padding-left: 10px;
}

.icon-box-text {
  text-align: left; 
  font-style: oblique;
  display: inline-block;
  width: 260px;
  font-size: 15px;
  vertical-align: middle;
  padding-left: 10px;
  word-wrap: break-word;
}

.left {
  float: left;
}

.right {
  float: right; 
}

.center {
  margin: auto;
  width: 100%;
  text-align: center;
}


/* Conversation bubble stuff */

.conversations {

}

#conversation-container {
  max-height: 400px !important;
  overflow-y: auto !important; 
  padding-left: 10px;
}

#conversation-container::-webkit-scrollbar-track
{
  -webkit-box-shadow: inset 0 0 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.3);
  background-color: #F5F5F5;
  border-radius: 10px;
}

#conversation-container::-webkit-scrollbar
{
  width: 10px;
  background-color: #F5F5F5;
}

#conversation-container::-webkit-scrollbar-track-piece {
  background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8);
}

#conversation-container::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb
{
  border-radius: 10px;
  background-image: -webkit-gradient(linear,
    left bottom,
    left top,
    color-stop(0.44, rgb(122,153,217)),
    color-stop(0.72, rgb(73,125,189)),
    color-stop(0.86, rgb(28,58,148)));
}

.talk-bubble {
  margin-left: 10px;
  margin-right: 30px;
  display: inline-block;
  position: relative;
  /* width: 200px; */
  height: auto;
}

.border{
  border: 8px solid #666;
}

.outbound {
  background: rgb(43, 110, 175);
}

.inbound {
  background: #E4151A;
}

.round{
  border-radius: 5px;
  -webkit-border-radius: 5px;
  -moz-border-radius: 5px;

}

.tri-right.border.left-in:before {
  content: ' ';
  position: absolute;
  width: 0;
  height: 0;
  left: -10px;
  right: auto;
  top: 60%;
  bottom: auto;
  border: 20px solid;
  border-color: #666 #666 transparent transparent;
}
.tri-right.left-in:after{
  content: ' ';
  position: absolute;
  width: 0;
  height: 0;
  left: -20px;
  right: auto;
  top: 10%;
  bottom: auto;
  border: 12px solid;
  border-color: #E4151A #E4151A transparent transparent
}

.tri-right.border.right-in:before {
  content: ' ';
  position: absolute;
  width: 0;
  height: 0;
  left: auto;
  right: -40px;
  top: 30px;
  bottom: auto;
  border: 20px solid;
  border-color: #666 transparent transparent #666;
}
.tri-right.right-in:after{
  content: ' ';
  position: absolute;
  width: 0;
  height: 0;
  left: auto;
  right: -20px;
  top: 10%;
  bottom: auto;
  border: 12px solid;
  border-color: rgb(43, 110, 175) transparent transparent rgb(43, 110, 175);
}

/* talk bubble contents */
.talktext{
  padding: .4em;
  text-align: left;
  /* line-height: 1.5em; */
}
.talktext p{
  -webkit-margin-before: 0em;
  -webkit-margin-after: 0em;
}</css><name>echo-showcase</name><sys_class_name>sp_css</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>jc</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2017-03-16 22:51:35</sys_created_on><sys_customer_update>true</sys_customer_update><sys_id>ef7c5e65db2d3a00d1a9f1351d9619a4</sys_id><sys_mod_count>55</sys_mod_count><sys_name>echo-showcase</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Amazon Echo" source="x_snc_amazon_echo">101eb7da13a21200d0143d622244b063</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_replace_on_upgrade>false</sys_replace_on_upgrade><sys_scope display_value="Amazon Echo">101eb7da13a21200d0143d622244b063</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sp_css_ef7c5e65db2d3a00d1a9f1351d9619a4</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>jc</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2017-04-14 04:41:20</sys_updated_on></sp_css></record_update>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_metadata_link"><sys_metadata_link action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><directory>unload</directory><documentkey>5b25fe0edb5db200d1a9f1351d961930</documentkey><payload><?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<record_update table="x_snc_amazon_echo_intent">
    <x_snc_amazon_echo_intent action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE">
        <active>false</active>
        <always_available>false</always_available>
        <category/>
        <fallback>false</fallback>
        <intent_ends_session>false</intent_ends_session>
        <keyword>CheckStatusInc</keyword>
        <name>Check Status (Step 2)</name>
        <next_intent/>
        <order/>
        <output_speech_format/>
        <reprompt_speech_format/>
        <script><![CDATA[(function(content, attributes, erb){
	var num = "INC" + content.Number.value;
	
	var inc = new GlideRecord('incident');
	if (inc.get('number', num)){
		var updatedArr = inc.sys_updated_on.getDisplayValue().split(" ");
		var updatedDate = updatedArr[0];
		var updatedTime = updatedArr[1].split(":");
		updatedTime = updatedTime[0] + ":" + updatedTime[1];
		
		var notes = inc.comments.getJournalEntry(-1);
		var na = notes.split("\n\n");
		notes = na[0];
		
		//Message output...
		msg = "<speak>";
		msg += "The current status of your incident is: " + inc.state.getDisplayValue() + ". ";
		msg += "Your incident was last updated on: " + updatedDate + " at " + updatedTime  + ". ";
		
		if (notes != "" && notes != null) {
			notes = notes.split("\n");
			msg += "The last update was: " + notes[1] + ".";
		}
		
		msg += "</speak>";
		erb.setOutputSpeech("SSML", "", msg);
		//End message output
	} else {
		erb.setReprompt("PlainText", "I was unable to find that Incident. What was that Incident number again?");
	}
	erb.setEnd(true);
	
	result = erb.response;
})(content, attributes, new EchoResponseBuilder());]]></script>

<record_update table="x_snc_amazon_echo_intent">
    <x_snc_amazon_echo_intent action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE">
        <active>true</active>
        <always_available>false</always_available>
        <category/>
        <fallback>false</fallback>
        <intent_ends_session>false</intent_ends_session>
        <keyword>SecurityIncidents</keyword>
        <name>Hear Security Incidents</name>
        <next_intent>18ca4a53db0ef60015f2de01ce9619e8</next_intent>
        <order/>
        <output_speech_format>SSML</output_speech_format>
        <reprompt_speech_format/>
        <script><![CDATA[(function(current, content, attributes, ER, IntentUtils){
	var msg = '<speak>';
	var isCriticalPriority = false;

	var gr = new GlideRecord('sn_si_incident');
	gr.addEncodedQuery('active=true');
	gr.query();

	while (gr.next()){
		msg += IntentUtils.taskNumberToSSML(gr) + ' has a priority of ' + gr.priority.getDisplayValue() + " and is in the status of " + gr.state.getDisplayValue() + ". The description is " + gr.short_description + ". ";
		
		if (gr.priority.getDisplayValue() == '1 - Critical')
			isCriticalPriority = true;
	}
	
	if (isCriticalPriority) {
		msg += "One or more Security Incidents have a Critical priority. To hear more details about the Critical Security Incidents, say 'Hear Critical Security Incidents'";
	}

	msg += "</speak>";

	ER.setOutputSpeech(current.output_speech_format, "", msg);
	ER.setEnd(current.intent_ends_session);
	result = ER.response; //Required
})(current, content, attributes, new EchoResponseBuilder(), new IntentUtils());]]></script>

sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_metadata_link"><sys_metadata_link action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><directory>update</directory><documentkey>1dad2617db4ef60015f2de01ce961969</documentkey><payload><?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<record_update table="x_snc_amazon_echo_intent">
    <x_snc_amazon_echo_intent action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE">
        <active>true</active>
        <always_available>false</always_available>
        <category/>
        <fallback>false</fallback>
        <intent_ends_session>false</intent_ends_session>
        <keyword>PortfolioStatus</keyword>
        <name>What's the status of my IT Operations Portfolio?</name>
        <next_intent/>
        <order>600</order>
        <output_speech_format>SSML</output_speech_format>
        <reprompt_speech_format/>
        <script><![CDATA[(function(current, content, attributes, ER, IntentUtils){
	var msg = "<speak>";

	var p = new GlideRecord('pm_portfolio');
	if (!p.get('name', 'IT Operations'))
		msg += "Unable to find a portfolio called IT Operations. ";
	else {
		msg += "Here is the status of the IT Operations Portfolio, managed by" + p.portfolio_manager.getDisplayValue() + ", for Fiscal Year 17. "; 

		/***** Demands *****/
		var demand = new GlideAggregate('dmn_demand');
		demand.addEncodedQuery('portfolio=f9325e53933012003b4bb095e57ffb31^start_dateONThis year@javascript:gs.beginningOfThisYear()@javascript:gs.endOfThisYear()');
		demand.addAggregate('COUNT');
		demand.query();

		if (demand.next()){
			var cnt = demand.getAggregate('COUNT');
			msg += "There " + (cnt == 1 ? 'is ' : 'are ') + cnt + ' open Demands in the portfolio back-log. ';
		}

		/***** Projects *****/
		var project = new GlideAggregate('pm_m2m_portfolio_project');
		project.addAggregate('COUNT');
		project.addEncodedQuery('portfolio=f9325e53933012003b4bb095e57ffb31^project.pm_project.start_dateONThis year@javascript:gs.beginningOfThisYear()@javascript:gs.endOfThisYear()');
		project.query();

		if (project.next()){
			var prjCount = project.getAggregate('COUNT');
			msg += "There " + (prjCount == 1 ? 'is ' : 'are ') + prjCount + ' active Projects that have started this year. ';
		}

		/***** Portfolio Cost Defaults *****/
		var totalPortfolioTarget = 0;
		var totalPortfolioPlanned = 0;
		var totalPortfolioActuals = 2100000;

		/***** Portfolio Target Cost *****/ 
		var portfolioTarget = new GlideRecord('project_funding');
		portfolioTarget.addEncodedQuery('portfolio=f9325e53933012003b4bb095e57ffb31^programISEMPTY^taskISEMPTY^fiscal_period.nameLIKEFY17');
		portfolioTarget.query();

		if (portfolioTarget.next())
			totalPortfolioTarget = portfolioTarget.target;

		/***** Portfolio Planned Cost *****/
		var fundings = [];

		var funding = new GlideRecord('project_funding');
		funding.addEncodedQuery('portfolio=f9325e53933012003b4bb095e57ffb31^fiscal_period=795985d4133002003ff3691c2c6a5e6f^planned=true');
		funding.query();

		while (funding.next())
			fundings.push(funding.task.sys_id.toString());

		var costPlan = new GlideAggregate('cost_plan');
		costPlan.addQuery('portfolio', 'f9325e53933012003b4bb095e57ffb31');
		costPlan.addQuery('task', 'IN', fundings);
		costPlan.addAggregate('SUM', 'cost_local_currency');
		costPlan.setGroup(false);
		costPlan.query();
		if (costPlan.next()) 
			totalPortfolioPlanned = costPlan.getAggregate('SUM', 'cost_local_currency');
		
		/***** Portfolio Actual Cost *****/
		
		
		msg += "The portfolio target budget is $" + totalPortfolioTarget + ". ";
		msg += "The total planned cost for this portfolio is $" + totalPortfolioPlanned + ". ";
		msg += "The actual cost as of today for this portfolio is $" + totalPortfolioActuals + ". "
		msg += "This portfolio is at " + ((totalPortfolioActuals/totalPortfolioTarget)*100) + "% of the budget and presents a financial risk. Reach out to the portfolio manager " + p.portfolio_manager.getDisplayValue() + " for a more detailed cost analysis.";
	}

	msg += "</speak>";
	
	ER.setOutputSpeech(current.output_speech_format, "", msg);
	ER.setEnd(current.intent_ends_session);
	
	result = ER.response; //Required
})(current, content, attributes, new EchoResponseBuilder(), new IntentUtils());]]></script>

        <slot_name_3/>

<record_update table="x_snc_amazon_echo_intent">
    <x_snc_amazon_echo_intent action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE">
        <active>true</active>
        <always_available>false</always_available>
        <category/>
        <fallback>false</fallback>
        <intent_ends_session>false</intent_ends_session>
        <keyword>MyRequests</keyword>
        <name>My Requests</name>
        <next_intent/>
        <order>200</order>
        <output_speech_format/>
        <reprompt_speech_format/>
        <script><![CDATA[(function(content, attributes, erb){
	var introMessage = 'Here is a list of your open Service Requests: ';
	var outroMessage = '';
	var msg = '';
	var hasRITMs = false;
	
	var usr = 'f7c7610d13b69200d0143d622244b053'; //For demo purposes
	
	var ritm = new GlideRecord('sc_req_item');
	ritm.addQuery('opened_by', usr);
	ritm.query();
	
	while (ritm.next()){
		var updatedArr = ritm.due_date.getDisplayValue().split(" ");
		var updatedDate = updatedArr[0];
		var updatedTime = updatedArr[1].split(":");
		updatedTime = updatedTime[0] + ":" + updatedTime[1];
		
		var num = ritm.number.toString();
		var numS = num.slice(-7);
		
		introMessage += "Request <say-as interpret-as='spell-out'>" + "RITM" + "</say-as> <say-as interpret-as='digits'>" + numS + "</say-as> for a " +  ritm.cat_item.getDisplayValue() +  " is in the status of: " + ritm.stage + ". ";
		introMessage += "The requested due date is: " + updatedDate + " at " + updatedTime + ". ";
		hasRITMs = true;
	}
	
	if (!hasRITMs)
		introMessage = "You have no open Service Requests. ";
	
	outroMessage += "To hear the list of requests again, say 'hear requests'. To go back to the status for today, say 'What's happening today'.";
	msg = "<speak>" + introMessage + outroMessage + "</speak>";
	
	erb.setOutputSpeech("SSML", null, msg);
	erb.setEnd(false);
	
	result = erb.getResponse();
	
})(content, attributes, new EchoResponseBuilder());]]></script>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_metadata_link"><sys_metadata_link action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><directory>update</directory><documentkey>b952ada6db8ef600d1a9f1351d961902</documentkey><payload><?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<record_update table="x_snc_amazon_echo_intent">
    <x_snc_amazon_echo_intent action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE">
        <active>true</active>
        <always_available>false</always_available>
        <category/>
        <fallback>false</fallback>
        <intent_ends_session>false</intent_ends_session>
        <keyword>SecurityThreatStatus</keyword>
        <name>Are there any Security threats?</name>
        <next_intent>9f270c36db463a00d1a9f1351d96195d</next_intent>
        <order>500</order>
        <output_speech_format>SSML</output_speech_format>
        <reprompt_speech_format/>
        <script><![CDATA[(function(current, content, attributes, ER, IntentUtils){	
	var sirCount = 0;
	var vulnCount = 0;
	var msg = '<speak>';

	var ga = new GlideAggregate('sn_si_incident');
	ga.addEncodedQuery('priority=1');
	ga.addAggregate('COUNT');
	ga.query();
	if (ga.next()) 
		sirCount = ga.getAggregate('COUNT');

	if (sirCount > 0)
		msg += "There " + (sirCount > 1 ? 'are' : 'is') + " <say-as interpret-as='cardinal'>" + sirCount + "</say-as> open, critical Security Incidents. ";

	ga = new GlideAggregate('sn_vul_vulnerable_item');
	ga.addEncodedQuery('priority=1');
	ga.addAggregate('COUNT');
	ga.query();
	if (ga.next()) 
		vulnCount = ga.getAggregate('COUNT');	

	if (vulnCount > 0)
		msg += "There " + (vulnCount > 1 ? 'are' : 'is')  + " <say-as interpret-as='cardinal'>" + vulnCount + "</say-as> critical-priority Vulnerable item" + (vulnCount > 1 ? 's' : '') + ". ";

	msg += "To hear more information, say ";
	msg += "'Hear Security Incidents' or 'Hear Vulnerable Items'. ";
	msg += '</speak>';

	ER.setOutputSpeech(current.output_speech_format, "", msg);
	//ER.setReprompt("PlainText/SSML", "Text goes here", "SSML goes here");
	//ER.setAttributes(attrObj); = Object of session attributes

	ER.setEnd(current.intent_ends_session);

	result = ER.response; 

})(current, content, attributes, new EchoResponseBuilder(), new IntentUtils());]]></script>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_metadata_link"><sys_metadata_link action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><directory>unload</directory><documentkey>65b172cadb5db200d1a9f1351d9619b3</documentkey><payload><?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<record_update table="x_snc_amazon_echo_intent">
    <x_snc_amazon_echo_intent action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE">
        <active>true</active>
        <always_available>false</always_available>
        <category/>
        <fallback>false</fallback>
        <intent_ends_session>false</intent_ends_session>
        <keyword>WhatsHappeningChanges</keyword>
        <name>What's happening? (Changes)</name>
        <next_intent/>
        <order/>
        <output_speech_format/>
        <reprompt_speech_format/>
        <script><![CDATA[(function(content, attributes, erb){
	var introMessage = "Here is a list of Changes to be implemented today: ";
	var outroMessage = '';
	var msg = '';
	var hasChanges = false;
	
	var chg = new GlideRecord('change_request');
	chg.addEncodedQuery('start_dateONToday@javascript:gs.daysAgoStart(0)@javascript:gs.daysAgoEnd(0)^active=true');
	chg.query();
	
	while (chg.next()){		
		var updatedArr = chg.end_date.getDisplayValue().split(" ");
		var updatedDate = updatedArr[0];
		var updatedTime = updatedArr[1].split(":");
		updatedTime = updatedTime[0] + ":" + updatedTime[1];
		
		var num = chg.number.toString();
		var numS = num.slice(-7);		
		
		var chgNum = "<say-as interpret-as='spell-out'>" + "CHG" + "</say-as> <say-as interpret-as='digits'>" + numS + "</say-as>";		
		
		introMessage += "Change " + chgNum + " is a " + chg.type.getDisplayValue() + " Change affecting the " + chg.cmdb_ci.getDisplayValue() + " Configuration Item. ";
		introMessage += "The current risk value is: " + chg.risk.getDisplayValue() + ". ";
		introMessage += "The purpose of the change is: " + chg.short_description + ". ";
		introMessage += "This change is scheduled to end on " + updatedDate + " at " + updatedTime + ". ";
		hasChanges = true;
	}
	
	
	if (!hasChanges)
		introMessage = "There are no Changes scheduled to be implemented today. ";
	
	outroMessage += "To hear the list of Changes again, say 'hear Changes'. To go back to the status for today, say 'What's happening today'.";
	
	msg = "<speak>" + introMessage + outroMessage + "</speak>";
	
	erb.setOutputSpeech("SSML", "", msg);
	erb.setEnd(false);
	
	result = erb.getResponse();
	
})(content, attributes, new EchoResponseBuilder());]]></script>

        <sys_mod_count>1</sys_mod_count>
        <sys_updated_by>jc</sys_updated_by>
        <sys_updated_on>2017-03-06 03:52:59</sys_updated_on>
        <top_level_intent>false</top_level_intent>

    <x_snc_amazon_echo_intent action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE">
        <active>true</active>
        <always_available>false</always_available>
        <category/>
        <fallback>false</fallback>
        <intent_ends_session>false</intent_ends_session>
        <keyword>ThisWeeksChanges</keyword>
        <name>Are there any Changes this week?</name>
        <next_intent/>
        <order>400</order>
        <output_speech_format/>
        <reprompt_speech_format/>
        <script><![CDATA[(function(content, attributes, erb){
	//This returned an invalid SSML error. gotta check this...
	
	var introMessage = "Here is a list of Changes to be implemented this week: ";
	var outroMessage = '';
	var msg = '';
	var hasChanges = false;
	
	var chg = new GlideRecord('change_request');
	chg.addEncodedQuery('active=true^start_dateONThis week@javascript:gs.beginningOfThisWeek()@javascript:gs.endOfThisWeek()');
	chg.query();
	
	while (chg.next()){		
		var updatedArr = chg.end_date.getDisplayValue().split(" ");
		var updatedDate = updatedArr[0];
		var updatedTime = updatedArr[1].split(":");
		updatedTime = updatedTime[0] + ":" + updatedTime[1];
		
		var num = chg.number.toString();
		var numS = num.slice(-7);		
		
		var chgNum = "<say-as interpret-as='spell-out'>" + "CHG" + "</say-as> <say-as interpret-as='digits'>" + numS + "</say-as>";
		
		introMessage += "Change " + chgNum + " is a " + chg.type.getDisplayValue() + " Change affecting the " + chg.cmdb_ci.getDisplayValue() + " Configuration Item. ";
		introMessage += "The current risk value is: " + chg.risk.getDisplayValue() + ". ";
		introMessage += "The purpose of the change is: " + chg.short_description + ". ";
		introMessage += "This change is scheduled to end on " + updatedDate + " at " + updatedTime + ". ";
		hasChanges = true;
	}
	
	
	if (!hasChanges)
		introMessage = "There are no Changes scheduled to be implemented today. ";
	
	outroMessage += "To hear the list of Changes again, say 'This Weeks Changes'.";
	
	msg = "<speak>" + introMessage + outroMessage + "</speak>";
	
	erb.setOutputSpeech("SSML", "", msg);
	erb.setEnd(false);
	
	result = erb.getResponse();
	
})(content, attributes, new EchoResponseBuilder());]]></script>

<record_update table="x_snc_amazon_echo_intent">
    <x_snc_amazon_echo_intent action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE">
        <active>true</active>
        <always_available>false</always_available>
        <category/>
        <fallback>false</fallback>
        <intent_ends_session>false</intent_ends_session>
        <keyword>WhatsHappeningIncidents</keyword>
        <name>What's happening? (P1 Incidents)</name>
        <next_intent/>
        <order/>
        <output_speech_format/>
        <reprompt_speech_format/>
        <script><![CDATA[(function(content, attributes, erb){
	var introMessage = "Here is a list of today's Priority One Incidents: ";
	var outroMessage = '';
	var msg = '';
	
	var inc = new GlideRecord('incident');
	inc.addEncodedQuery('active=true^priority=1');
	inc.query();
	
	while (inc.next()){		
		var updatedArr = inc.sys_updated_on.getDisplayValue().split(" ");
		var updatedDate = updatedArr[0];
		var updatedTime = updatedArr[1].split(":");
		updatedTime = updatedTime[0] + ":" + updatedTime[1];
		
		var num = inc.number.toString();
		var numS = num.slice(-7);		
		
		var incNum = "<say-as interpret-as='spell-out'>" + "INC" + "</say-as> <say-as interpret-as='digits'>" + numS + "</say-as>";	
		
		introMessage += "Incident " + incNum + (inc.cmdb_ci != '' ? (" is currently impacting the " + inc.cmdb_ci.getDisplayValue() + " configuration item. ") : (" does not yet have a CI associated with it. "));
		introMessage += "The description of this incident is: " + inc.short_description + ". ";
		introMessage += "The current status of this incident is: " + inc.state.getDisplayValue() + ". ";
		introMessage += "This incident was last updated on " + updatedDate + " at " + updatedTime + ". ";
		
	}
	
	outroMessage += "To hear the list of incidents again, say 'hear incidents'. To go back to the status for today, say 'What's happening today'.";
	
	msg = "<speak>" + introMessage + outroMessage + "</speak>";
	
	erb.setOutputSpeech("SSML", "", msg);
	//erb.setReprompt("SSML", "", "<speak>" + outroMessage + "</speak>");
	erb.setEnd(false);
	
	result = erb.getResponse();
	
})(content, attributes, new EchoResponseBuilder());]]></script>

<record_update table="x_snc_amazon_echo_utterance">
    <x_snc_amazon_echo_utterance action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE">
        <active>true</active>
        <keyword>CheckStatusInc</keyword>
        <name>CheckStatus Step 2</name>
        <next/>
        <script><![CDATA[(function(content, attributes, erb){
	var num = "INC" + content.Number.value;
	
	var inc = new GlideRecord('incident');
	if (inc.get('number', num)){
		var updatedArr = inc.sys_updated_on.getDisplayValue().split(" ");
		var updatedDate = updatedArr[0];
		var updatedTime = updatedArr[1].split(":");
		updatedTime = updatedTime[0] + ":" + updatedTime[1];
		
		var notes = inc.comments.getJournalEntry(-1);
		var na = notes.split("\n\n");
		notes = na[0];
		
		//Message output...
		msg = "<speak>";
		msg += "The current status of your incident is: " + inc.state.getDisplayValue() + ". ";
		msg += "Your incident was last updated on: " + updatedDate + " at " + updatedTime  + ". ";
		
		if (notes != "" && notes != null) {
			notes = notes.split("\n");
			msg += "The last update was: " + notes[1] + ".";
		}
		
		msg += "</speak>";
		erb.setOutputSpeech("SSML", "", msg);
		//End message output
	} else {
		erb.setReprompt("PlainText", "I was unable to find that Incident. What was that Incident number again?");
	}
	erb.setEnd(true);
	
	result = erb.getResponse();
	
	
	
})(content, attributes, new EchoResponseBuilder());]]></script>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>package_private</access><active>true</active><api_name>x_snc_amazon_echo.EchoConversation</api_name><client_callable>false</client_callable><description>Amazon Echo App:
Used by the Conversation widget in Service Portal</description><name>EchoConversation</name><script><![CDATA[var EchoConversation = Class.create();
EchoConversation.prototype = {
	initialize: function() {
		this.limiter = 3;
		this.recentConversations = this.getRecentConversations();
	},

	getRecentConversations : function(limiter) {
		if (!limiter)
			limiter = this.limiter;

		var conversations = [];
		var pointer = 0;

		var log = new GlideRecord('x_snc_amazon_echo_log');
		log.addQuery('type', 'Outbound');
		log.setLimit(limiter);
		log.orderByDesc('sys_created_on');
		log.query();
		

		while (log.next()){
			pointer++;
			var C = {};
			C.order = pointer;
			C.inbound = log.in_response_to.spoken_phrase + '';
			C.outbound = log.spoken_phrase + '';	
			conversations.push(C);
		}
		
		return conversations;
	},

	type: 'EchoConversation'

        <script><![CDATA[(function(current, content, attributes, ER, IntentUtils){
	var msg = '<speak>';

	var gr = new GlideRecord('sn_si_incident');
	gr.addEncodedQuery('active=true^priority=1');
	gr.query();

	while (gr.next()){
		msg += "Incident " + IntentUtils.taskNumberToSSML(gr);
		msg += (!gr.assigned_to ? " is unassigned " : (' is assigned to ' + gr.assigned_to.getDisplayValue() + ', '));
		var updatedDateTime = IntentUtils.formatDateTime(gr.sys_updated_on);

		msg += 'and was last updated on ' + updatedDateTime.date + ' at ' + updatedDateTime.time + '. ';

		msg += "The last update was: " + IntentUtils.getLastCommentOrWorkNote('comments', gr);
	}

	msg += "</speak>";

	ER.setOutputSpeech(current.output_speech_format, "", msg);
	ER.setEnd(current.intent_ends_session);
	result = ER.response; //Required
})(current, content, attributes, new EchoResponseBuilder(), new IntentUtils());]]></script>

	var gr = new GlideRecord('sn_vul_vulnerable_item');
	gr.addEncodedQuery('active=true^priority=1');
	gr.query();

	while (gr.next()){
		msg += "Vulnerable item " + IntentUtils.taskNumberToSSML(gr);
		msg += (!gr.assigned_to ? " is unassigned " : (' is assigned to ' + gr.assigned_to.getDisplayValue() + ', '));
		var updatedDateTime = IntentUtils.formatDateTime(gr.sys_updated_on);
		msg += 'and was last updated on ' + updatedDateTime.date + ' at ' + updatedDateTime.time + '. ';
		msg += "The last update was: " + IntentUtils.getLastCommentOrWorkNote('work_notes', gr) + ". ";
		
		msg += "The affected Configuration Item is: " + gr.cmdb_ci.getDisplayValue() + '. ';

		var affectedSvc = new GlideAggregate('task_cmdb_ci_service');
		affectedSvc.addQuery('task', gr.sys_id);
		affectedSvc.addQuery('cmdb_ci_service.busines_criticality', '1 - most critical');
		affectedSvc.addAggregate('COUNT');
		affectedSvc.query();


		if (affectedSvc.next())
			affectedSvcCount = affectedSvc.getAggregate('COUNT');

		if (affectedSvcCount > 0){
			msg += "This Vulnerable item is impacting " + affectedSvcCount + " Critical services, which could result in significant business impact. You may want to consider auto-remediation. To attempt to auto-remediate this Vulnerability, say 'Run Remediation Workflow'.";
		}

	}

	msg += "</speak>";

	ER.setOutputSpeech(current.output_speech_format, "", msg);
	ER.setEnd(current.intent_ends_session);
	result = ER.response; //Required
})(current, content, attributes, new EchoResponseBuilder(), new IntentUtils());]]></script>

<record_update table="x_snc_amazon_echo_intent">
    <x_snc_amazon_echo_intent action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE">
        <active>true</active>
        <always_available>false</always_available>
        <category/>
        <fallback>false</fallback>
        <intent_ends_session>false</intent_ends_session>
        <keyword>SecurityIncidents</keyword>
        <name>Hear Security Incidents</name>
        <next_intent>18ca4a53db0ef60015f2de01ce9619e8</next_intent>
        <order/>
        <output_speech_format>SSML</output_speech_format>
        <reprompt_speech_format/>
        <script><![CDATA[(function(current, content, attributes, ER, IntentUtils){
	var msg = '<speak>';
	var isCriticalPriority = false;

	var gr = new GlideRecord('sn_si_incident');
	gr.addEncodedQuery('active=true');
	gr.query();

	while (gr.next()){
		msg += IntentUtils.taskNumberToSSML(gr) + ' has a priority of ' + gr.priority.getDisplayValue() + " and is in the status of " + gr.state.getDisplayValue() + ". The description is " + gr.short_description + ". ";
		
		if (gr.priority.getDisplayValue() == '1 - Critical')
			isCriticalPriority = true;
	}
	
	if (isCriticalPriority) {
		msg += "One or more Security Incidents have a Critical priority. To hear more details about the Critical Security Incidents, say 'Hear Critical Security Incidents'";
	}

	msg += "</speak>";

	ER.setOutputSpeech(current.output_speech_format, "", msg);
	ER.setEnd(current.intent_ends_session);
	result = ER.response; //Required
})(current, content, attributes, new EchoResponseBuilder(), new IntentUtils());]]></script>

<record_update table="x_snc_amazon_echo_intent">
    <x_snc_amazon_echo_intent action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE">
        <active>true</active>
        <always_available>true</always_available>
        <category/>
        <fallback>false</fallback>
        <intent_ends_session>false</intent_ends_session>
        <keyword>WhatsHappening</keyword>
        <name>What's happening today?</name>
        <next_intent>65b172cadb5db200d1a9f1351d9619b3,778172cadb5db200d1a9f1351d9619b9,54cdae0adb5db200d1a9f1351d9619d1</next_intent>
        <order>100</order>
        <output_speech_format/>
        <reprompt_speech_format/>
        <script><![CDATA[(function(content, attributes, erb, current){
		
	var introMessage = "Here's what's happening today: ";
	var outroMessage = ' ';
	var msg = '';
	
	//Service Interruptions
	var gaO = new GlideAggregate('cmdb_ci_outage');
	gaO.addAggregate('COUNT');
	gaO.addEncodedQuery('begin<javascript:gs.daysAgoStart(0)^endISEMPTY^typeINdegradation,outage');
	gaO.query();
	
	var outages = 0;
	if (gaO.next())
		outages = gaO.getAggregate('COUNT');
	
	if (outages > 0) {
		introMessage += "There " + (outages > 1 ? "are " : "is ") + outages +
		(outages > 1 ? " Outages or Service Interruptions " : " Outage or Service Interruption ") +
		" impacting services today. ";
		outroMessage += "To hear the outage details, say 'Hear Outages. '";
	}
	
	//P1 incidents
	var gaI = new GlideAggregate('incident');
	gaI.addAggregate('COUNT');
	gaI.addEncodedQuery('active=true^priority=1');
	gaI.query();
	var incidents = 0;
	if (gaI.next())
		incidents = gaI.getAggregate('COUNT');
	
	if (incidents > 0) {
		introMessage += "There " + (incidents > 1 ? "are " : "is ") + incidents +
		(incidents > 1 ? " active Priority One incidents." : " active Priority One incident.");
		outroMessage += "To hear the Priority one incident details, say 'Hear Incidents. '";
	}
	
	
	//Changes
	var gaC = new GlideAggregate('change_request');
	gaC.addAggregate('COUNT');
	gaC.addEncodedQuery('start_dateONToday@javascript:gs.daysAgoStart(0)@javascript:gs.daysAgoEnd(0)^active=true');
	gaC.query();
	var changes = 0;
	if (gaC.next())
		changes = gaC.getAggregate('COUNT');

	if (changes > 0) {
		introMessage += "There " + (changes > 1 ? "are " : "is ") + changes +
		(changes > 1 ? " changes " : " change ") +
		'scheduled for implementation today';	
		outroMessage += "To hear the Change details, say 'Hear Changes. '";
	}
	
	if (incidents == 0 && outages == 0 && changes == 0){
		introMessage += 'It looks like there are no interruptions, Priority one incidents or changes scheduled today. Relax and take a load off.';
	}
	
	msg = "<speak>" + introMessage + outroMessage + "</speak>";

	erb.setOutputSpeech("SSML", "", msg);
	erb.setReprompt("SSML", "", "<speak>" + outroMessage + "</speak>");
	erb.setEnd(false);
	
	result = erb.getResponse();
	
})(content, attributes, new EchoResponseBuilder(), current);]]></script>

sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>package_private</access><active>true</active><api_name>x_snc_amazon_echo.IntentUtils</api_name><client_callable>false</client_callable><description>This is a utility script passed into Intent records that can be used to for constructing the result. Custom functions can be added her to perform new actions if needed.</description><name>IntentUtils</name><script><![CDATA[var IntentUtils = Class.create();
IntentUtils.prototype = {
	initialize: function() {
		this.TABLES = {
			INTENT : 'x_snc_amazon_echo_intent'
		};
		
	},

	taskNumberToSSML : function(taskGR) {
		var ssml = "";
		var num = new GlideRecord('sys_number');
		if (num.get('category', taskGR.getTableName())){
			ssml += '<say-as interpret-as="characters">' + num.prefix + '</say-as>';

			var prefixLength = num.prefix.toString();
			prefixLength = prefixLength.length;
			var numberLength = num.maximum_digits;

			ssml += '<say-as interpret-as="digits">' + taskGR.number.substring(prefixLength, numberLength + prefixLength) + '</say-as>';

		} else {
			gs.info("Unable to find number record for GR or taskGR is not a valid GlideRecord.");
		}
		return ssml;
	},

	formatDateTime : function(dt) {
		var updatedArr = dt.getDisplayValue().split(" ");
		var updatedDate = updatedArr[0];
		var updatedTime = updatedArr[1].split(":");
		updatedTime = updatedTime[0] + ":" + updatedTime[1];

		return {
			date : updatedDate,
			time : updatedTime
		};
	},

	getLastCommentOrWorkNote : function(type, gr) {
		var notes = gr[type].getJournalEntry(1);
		var na = notes.split("\n\n");
		notes = na[0];

		if (notes != "" && notes != null)
			notes = notes.split("\n");

		return notes[1];
	},

	getOrderedTopLevelIntentArrayNames : function() {
		var array = [];
		
		var gr = new GlideRecord(this.TABLES.INTENT);
		gr.addEncodedQuery('active=true^top_level_intent=true');
		gr.orderBy('order');
		gr.query();
		
		while (gr.next())
			array.push(gr.getDisplayValue());

		return array;
	},


	type: 'IntentUtils'
};]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_include</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>jc</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2017-04-13 20:25:30</sys_created_on><sys_customer_update>true</sys_customer_update><sys_id>eb370a6edbcef600d1a9f1351d96199c</sys_id><sys_mod_count>27</sys_mod_count><sys_name>IntentUtils</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Amazon Echo" source="x_snc_amazon_echo">101eb7da13a21200d0143d622244b063</sys_package><sys_policy>read</sys_policy><sys_replace_on_upgrade>false</sys_replace_on_upgrade><sys_scope display_value="Amazon Echo">101eb7da13a21200d0143d622244b063</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_include_eb370a6edbcef600d1a9f1351d96199c</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>jc</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2017-04-19 15:50:43</sys_updated_on></sys_script_include></record_update>

<record_update table="x_snc_amazon_echo_intent">
    <x_snc_amazon_echo_intent action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE">
        <active>true</active>
        <always_available>true</always_available>
        <category/>
        <fallback>false</fallback>
        <intent_ends_session>false</intent_ends_session>
        <keyword>RunRemediationWorkflow</keyword>
        <name>Run Remediation Workflow</name>
        <next_intent/>
        <order/>
        <output_speech_format>SSML</output_speech_format>
        <reprompt_speech_format/>
        <script><![CDATA[(function(current, content, attributes, ER, IntentUtils){
	var msg = '<speak>';

	msg += "Workflow 'Get Latest OS Patches' has been executed against the affected CI. When the workflow completes the work notes will be updated with the status of the remediation. Check the Vulnerable Item again soon."
	
	msg += "</speak>";

	ER.setOutputSpeech(current.output_speech_format, "", msg);
	ER.setEnd(current.intent_ends_session);
	result = ER.response; //Required
})(current, content, attributes, new EchoResponseBuilder(), new IntentUtils());]]></script>

sys_update_xml.name: sys_script_include_3338864adbd9b200d1a9f1351d9619c0
sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>public</access><active>true</active><api_name>x_snc_amazon_echo.EchoSkillDataGenerator</api_name><client_callable>false</client_callable><description/><name>EchoSkillDataGenerator</name><script><![CDATA[var EchoSkillDataGenerator = Class.create();
EchoSkillDataGenerator.prototype = {
	initialize: function() {
	},

	generateIntentSchema : function() {
		var schema = {};
		schema.intents = [];

		var intent = new GlideRecord('x_snc_amazon_echo_intent');
		intent.addQuery('active', 'true');
		intent.query();

		while (intent.next()){
			var currentIntent = {
				intent : intent.keyword + ''
			};

			var slots = this._setSlotArray(intent);
			if (slots.length != 0)
				currentIntent.slots = slots;

			schema.intents.push(currentIntent);
		}

		return JSON.stringify(schema, null, 4);
	},

	generateUtterances : function() {
		var utterances = "";
		var tempKeyword = "";

		var phrase = new GlideRecord('x_snc_amazon_echo_phrases');
		phrase.addQuery('active', 'true');
		phrase.addQuery('intent.active', 'true');
		phrase.orderByDesc('intent');
		phrase.query();
		
		while (phrase.next()){
			if (tempKeyword != "" && tempKeyword != phrase.intent.keyword)
				utterances += "\n";
			
			utterances += phrase.intent.keyword +  " " + phrase.getDisplayValue() + "\n";
			tempKeyword = phrase.intent.keyword;
		}
		
		return utterances;
	},

	_setSlotArray : function(current){
		var tempSlots = [];

		if (current.slot_name_1 != '' && current.slot_type_1 != ''){
			tempSlots.push({
				"name" : current.slot_name_1 + '',
				"type" : current.slot_type_1.getDisplayValue() + ''
			});
		}

		if (current.slot_name_2 != '' && current.slot_type_2 != ''){
			tempSlots.push({
				"name" : current.slot_name_2 + '',
				"type" : current.slot_type_2.getDisplayValue() + ''
			});
		}

		if (current.slot_name_3 != '' && current.slot_type_3 != ''){
			tempSlots.push({
				"name" : current.slot_name_3 + '',
				"type" : current.slot_type_3.getDisplayValue() + ''
			});
		}

		return tempSlots;
	},

	type: 'EchoSkillDataGenerator'
};]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_include</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>jc</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2017-03-06 00:30:27</sys_created_on><sys_customer_update>true</sys_customer_update><sys_id>3338864adbd9b200d1a9f1351d9619c0</sys_id><sys_mod_count>25</sys_mod_count><sys_name>EchoSkillDataGenerator</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Amazon Echo" source="x_snc_amazon_echo">101eb7da13a21200d0143d622244b063</sys_package><sys_policy>read</sys_policy><sys_replace_on_upgrade>false</sys_replace_on_upgrade><sys_scope display_value="Amazon Echo">101eb7da13a21200d0143d622244b063</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_include_3338864adbd9b200d1a9f1351d9619c0</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>jc</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2017-04-16 05:41:18</sys_updated_on></sys_script_include></record_update>

<record_update table="x_snc_amazon_echo_intent">
    <x_snc_amazon_echo_intent action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE">
        <active>true</active>
        <always_available>false</always_available>
        <category/>
        <fallback>false</fallback>
        <intent_ends_session>false</intent_ends_session>
        <keyword>MyRequests</keyword>
        <name>My Requests</name>
        <next_intent/>
        <order>200</order>
        <output_speech_format/>
        <reprompt_speech_format/>
        <script><![CDATA[(function(content, attributes, erb){
	var introMessage = 'Here is a list of your open Service Requests: ';
	var outroMessage = '';
	var msg = '';
	var hasRITMs = false;
	
	var usr = 'f7c7610d13b69200d0143d622244b053'; //For demo purposes
	
	var ritm = new GlideRecord('sc_req_item');
	ritm.addQuery('opened_by', usr);
	ritm.query();
	
	while (ritm.next()){
		var updatedArr = ritm.due_date.getDisplayValue().split(" ");
		var updatedDate = updatedArr[0];
		var updatedTime = updatedArr[1].split(":");
		updatedTime = updatedTime[0] + ":" + updatedTime[1];
		
		var num = ritm.number.toString();
		var numS = num.slice(-7);
		
		introMessage += "Request <say-as interpret-as='spell-out'>" + "RITM" + "</say-as> <say-as interpret-as='digits'>" + numS + "</say-as> for a " +  ritm.cat_item.getDisplayValue() +  " is in the status of: " + ritm.stage + ". ";
		introMessage += "The requested due date is: " + updatedDate + " at " + updatedTime + ". ";
		hasRITMs = true;
	}
	
	if (!hasRITMs)
		introMessage = "You have no open Service Requests. ";
	
	outroMessage += "To hear the list of requests again, say 'hear requests'. To go back to the status for today, say 'What's happening today'.";
	msg = "<speak>" + introMessage + outroMessage + "</speak>";
	
	erb.setOutputSpeech("SSML", null, msg);
	erb.setEnd(false);
	
	result = erb.getResponse();
	
})(content, attributes, new EchoResponseBuilder());]]></script>

</record_update>

sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_metadata_link"><sys_metadata_link action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><directory>update</directory><documentkey>1756561bdb0ef60015f2de01ce961973</documentkey><payload><?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<record_update table="x_snc_amazon_echo_intent">
    <x_snc_amazon_echo_intent action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE">
        <active>true</active>
        <always_available>true</always_available>
        <category/>
        <fallback>false</fallback>
        <intent_ends_session>false</intent_ends_session>
        <keyword>CriticalVulnerabilities</keyword>
        <name>Hear Critical Vulnerable Items</name>
        <next_intent>58bb12dbdb0ef60015f2de01ce961901</next_intent>
        <order/>
        <output_speech_format>SSML</output_speech_format>
        <reprompt_speech_format/>
        <script><![CDATA[(function(current, content, attributes, ER, IntentUtils){
	var msg = '<speak>';
	var affectedSvcCount = 0;

	var gr = new GlideRecord('sn_vul_vulnerable_item');
	gr.addEncodedQuery('active=true^priority=1');
	gr.query();

	while (gr.next()){
		msg += "Vulnerable item " + IntentUtils.taskNumberToSSML(gr);
		msg += (!gr.assigned_to ? " is unassigned " : (' is assigned to ' + gr.assigned_to.getDisplayValue() + ', '));
		var updatedDateTime = IntentUtils.formatDateTime(gr.sys_updated_on);
		msg += 'and was last updated on ' + updatedDateTime.date + ' at ' + updatedDateTime.time + '. ';
		msg += "The last update was: " + IntentUtils.getLastCommentOrWorkNote('work_notes', gr) + ". ";
		
		msg += "The affected Configuration Item is: " + gr.cmdb_ci.getDisplayValue() + '. ';

		var affectedSvc = new GlideAggregate('task_cmdb_ci_service');
		affectedSvc.addQuery('task', gr.sys_id);
		affectedSvc.addQuery('cmdb_ci_service.busines_criticality', '1 - most critical');
		affectedSvc.addAggregate('COUNT');
		affectedSvc.query();


		if (affectedSvc.next())
			affectedSvcCount = affectedSvc.getAggregate('COUNT');

		if (affectedSvcCount > 0){
			msg += "This Vulnerable item is impacting " + affectedSvcCount + " Critical services, which could result in significant business impact. You may want to consider auto-remediation. To attempt to auto-remediate this Vulnerability, say 'Run Remediation Workflow'.";
		}

	}

	msg += "</speak>";

	ER.setOutputSpeech(current.output_speech_format, "", msg);
	ER.setEnd(current.intent_ends_session);
	result = ER.response; //Required
})(current, content, attributes, new EchoResponseBuilder(), new IntentUtils());]]></script>
        <slot_name_1/>
        <slot_name_2/>
        <slot_name_3/>
        <slot_type_1/>
        <slot_type_2/>
        <slot_type_3/>

        <sys_created_on>2017-04-16 05:25:29</sys_created_on>
        <sys_id>1756561bdb0ef60015f2de01ce961973</sys_id>
        <sys_mod_count>5</sys_mod_count>
        <sys_updated_by>jc</sys_updated_by>
        <sys_updated_on>2017-04-16 05:51:54</sys_updated_on>
        <top_level_intent>false</top_level_intent>
    </x_snc_amazon_echo_intent>
</record_update>

<record_update table="x_snc_amazon_echo_intent">
    <x_snc_amazon_echo_intent action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE">
        <active>true</active>
        <always_available>false</always_available>
        <category/>
        <fallback>false</fallback>
        <intent_ends_session>false</intent_ends_session>
        <keyword>WhatsHappeningIncidents</keyword>
        <name>What's happening? (P1 Incidents)</name>
        <next_intent/>
        <order/>
        <output_speech_format/>
        <reprompt_speech_format/>
        <script><![CDATA[(function(content, attributes, erb){
	var introMessage = "Here is a list of today's Priority One Incidents: ";
	var outroMessage = '';
	var msg = '';
	
	var inc = new GlideRecord('incident');
	inc.addEncodedQuery('active=true^priority=1');
	inc.query();
	
	while (inc.next()){		
		var updatedArr = inc.sys_updated_on.getDisplayValue().split(" ");
		var updatedDate = updatedArr[0];
		var updatedTime = updatedArr[1].split(":");
		updatedTime = updatedTime[0] + ":" + updatedTime[1];
		
		var num = inc.number.toString();
		var numS = num.slice(-7);		
		
		var incNum = "<say-as interpret-as='spell-out'>" + "INC" + "</say-as> <say-as interpret-as='digits'>" + numS + "</say-as>";	
		
		introMessage += "Incident " + incNum + (inc.cmdb_ci != '' ? (" is currently impacting the " + inc.cmdb_ci.getDisplayValue() + " configuration item. ") : (" does not yet have a CI associated with it. "));
		introMessage += "The description of this incident is: " + inc.short_description + ". ";
		introMessage += "The current status of this incident is: " + inc.state.getDisplayValue() + ". ";
		introMessage += "This incident was last updated on " + updatedDate + " at " + updatedTime + ". ";
		
	}
	
	outroMessage += "To hear the list of incidents again, say 'hear incidents'. To go back to the status for today, say 'What's happening today'.";
	
	msg = "<speak>" + introMessage + outroMessage + "</speak>";
	
	erb.setOutputSpeech("SSML", "", msg);
	//erb.setReprompt("SSML", "", "<speak>" + outroMessage + "</speak>");
	erb.setEnd(false);
	
	result = erb.getResponse();
	
})(content, attributes, new EchoResponseBuilder());]]></script>

<record_update table="x_snc_amazon_echo_intent">
    <x_snc_amazon_echo_intent action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE">
        <active>true</active>
        <always_available>false</always_available>
        <category/>
        <fallback>false</fallback>
        <intent_ends_session>false</intent_ends_session>
        <keyword>WhatsHappeningChanges</keyword>
        <name>What's happening? (Changes)</name>
        <next_intent/>
        <order/>
        <output_speech_format/>
        <reprompt_speech_format/>
        <script><![CDATA[(function(content, attributes, erb){
	var introMessage = "Here is a list of Changes to be implemented today: ";
	var outroMessage = '';
	var msg = '';
	var hasChanges = false;
	
	var chg = new GlideRecord('change_request');
	chg.addEncodedQuery('start_dateONToday@javascript:gs.daysAgoStart(0)@javascript:gs.daysAgoEnd(0)^active=true');
	chg.query();
	
	while (chg.next()){		
		var updatedArr = chg.end_date.getDisplayValue().split(" ");
		var updatedDate = updatedArr[0];
		var updatedTime = updatedArr[1].split(":");
		updatedTime = updatedTime[0] + ":" + updatedTime[1];
		
		var num = chg.number.toString();
		var numS = num.slice(-7);		
		
		var chgNum = "<say-as interpret-as='spell-out'>" + "CHG" + "</say-as> <say-as interpret-as='digits'>" + numS + "</say-as>";		
		
		introMessage += "Change " + chgNum + " is a " + chg.type.getDisplayValue() + " Change affecting the " + chg.cmdb_ci.getDisplayValue() + " Configuration Item. ";
		introMessage += "The current risk value is: " + chg.risk.getDisplayValue() + ". ";
		introMessage += "The purpose of the change is: " + chg.short_description + ". ";
		introMessage += "This change is scheduled to end on " + updatedDate + " at " + updatedTime + ". ";
		hasChanges = true;
	}
	
	
	if (!hasChanges)
		introMessage = "There are no Changes scheduled to be implemented today. ";
	
	outroMessage += "To hear the list of Changes again, say 'hear Changes'. To go back to the status for today, say 'What's happening today'.";
	
	msg = "<speak>" + introMessage + outroMessage + "</speak>";
	
	erb.setOutputSpeech("SSML", "", msg);
	erb.setEnd(false);
	
	result = erb.getResponse();
	
})(content, attributes, new EchoResponseBuilder());]]></script>

sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>package_private</access><active>true</active><api_name>x_snc_amazon_echo.EchoRequest</api_name><client_callable>false</client_callable><description/><name>EchoRequest</name><script><![CDATA[var EchoRequest = Class.create();
EchoRequest.prototype = {
	initialize: function(session, request) {
		//See request and session objects here: https://developer.amazon.com/public/solutions/alexa/alexa-skills-kit/docs/alexa-skills-kit-interface-reference
		
		//Request and Session variables
		this.request = request;
		this.REQUEST_TYPE = request.type;
		this.session = session;
				
		//Initializing defaults;
		this.intent_slots = {};
		this.session_attributes = {};
		
		
		this.intentRecord = this.getIntentRecord(); //Get intent record for current request
		this.isAllowedIntent = this._checkIfAllowedIntent();

		
		//TODO: Get last verbal command. See if this request is allowed by checking if it requires a previous command.
		this.lastCommand = this._getLastCommand();	
	},

	process: function() {
		if (!this.intentRecord)
			return;

		this.handleIntent(this.intentRecord);
	},

	getIntentRecord: function() {
		if (this.REQUEST_TYPE == 'LaunchRequest')
			keyword = 'LaunchRequest';
		else {
			keyword = this.request.intent.name;
			
			this.intent_slots = this.request.intent.slots;
			
			if (this.session.attributes)
				this.session_attributes = this.session.attributes;
		}

		var ir = new GlideRecord('x_snc_amazon_echo_intent');
		ir.addQuery('active', 'true');
		ir.addQuery('keyword', keyword);
		ir.query();

		if (ir.next())
			return ir;
		else
			this.setErrorResponse("Something went wrong. Could not find matching intent record in Intents table");

		return;
	},

	handleIntent: function(intent){		
		var evaluator = new GlideScopedEvaluator();
		evaluator.putVariable('content', this.intent_slots);
		evaluator.putVariable('attributes', this.session_attributes);
		evaluator.putVariable('current', intent);
		evaluator.putVariable('result', null);
		evaluator.evaluateScript(intent, 'script', null);
		var res = evaluator.getVariable('result');
				
		this.setResponse(res);
	},

	setResponse: function(response, isError) {
		this.response = response;

		if (this.REQUEST_TYPE != 'LaunchRequest')
			new x_snc_amazon_echo.EchoLog(this.session, this.request, this.response).log();

		return;
	},

	setErrorResponse : function(msg) {
		var erb = new EchoResponseBuilder();
		erb.setOutputSpeech("PlainText", msg);
		erb.setEnd(false);

		this.setResponse(erb.response, true);
	},

	_getLastCommand : function() {
		var sid = this.session.sessionId.substr(this.session.sessionId.indexOf(".") + 1);
		//TODO: Get last INBOUND log entry for this session. Check intent of that log to make sure current intent is a Next Intent for the previous. 
		
	},
	
	_checkIfAllowedIntent : function() {
		
	},

	type: 'EchoRequest'
};]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_include</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>jc</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2016-04-15 17:29:03</sys_created_on><sys_customer_update>true</sys_customer_update><sys_id>b90604bd13fe9200d0143d622244b067</sys_id><sys_mod_count>65</sys_mod_count><sys_name>EchoRequest</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Amazon Echo" source="x_snc_amazon_echo">101eb7da13a21200d0143d622244b063</sys_package><sys_policy>read</sys_policy><sys_replace_on_upgrade>false</sys_replace_on_upgrade><sys_scope display_value="Amazon Echo">101eb7da13a21200d0143d622244b063</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_include_b90604bd13fe9200d0143d622244b067</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>jc</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2017-04-16 07:22:05</sys_updated_on></sys_script_include></record_update>

<record_update table="x_snc_amazon_echo_intent">
    <x_snc_amazon_echo_intent action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE">
        <active>false</active>
        <always_available>false</always_available>
        <category/>
        <fallback>false</fallback>
        <intent_ends_session>false</intent_ends_session>
        <keyword>CreateIncident</keyword>
        <name>Create an Incident (Create)</name>
        <next_intent/>
        <order/>
        <output_speech_format/>
        <reprompt_speech_format/>
        <script><![CDATA[(function(content, attributes, erb){
	var issueText = content.Description.value;
	var userName = attributes.UserAttributes.name;
	
	var inc = new GlideRecord('incident');
	inc.initialize();
	inc.short_description = issueText;
	inc.description = "Opened by: " + userName + "\n" + issueText;
	inc.contact_type = "Alexa";
	var id = inc.insert();
	
	var incRec = new GlideRecord('incident');
	incRec.get(id);
	var number = incRec.number;
	
	var num = number.toString();
	var numS = num.slice(-7);
	
	var incNum = "<say-as interpret-as='spell-out'>" + "INC" + "</say-as> <say-as interpret-as='digits'>" + numS + "</say-as>";
	
	var ssml = "<speak>";
	ssml += "Your incident has been created. Here is your confirmation number: " + incNum;
	//ssml += "<say-as interpret-as='digits'>" + number +"</say-as>.";
	ssml += "</speak>";
	
	erb.setOutputSpeech("SSML", null, ssml);
	//erb.setReprompt("PlainText", "I didn't catch that. Tell me your issue by saying 'My issue is...' followed by your issue.", "");
	erb.setEnd(true);
	result = erb.response;
})(content, attributes, new EchoResponseBuilder());]]></script>

        <script><![CDATA[(function(current, content, attributes, ER, IntentUtils){

	var gr = new GlideRecord('cmdb_ci_outage');

	//ER.setAttributes(attrObj); = Object of session attributes
	ER.setEnd(current.intent_ends_session);

	result = ER.response; //Required
})(current, content, attributes, new EchoResponseBuilder(), new IntentUtils());]]></script>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_metadata_link"><sys_metadata_link action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><directory>update</directory><documentkey>778172cadb5db200d1a9f1351d9619b9</documentkey><payload><?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<record_update table="x_snc_amazon_echo_intent">
    <x_snc_amazon_echo_intent action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE">
        <active>true</active>
        <always_available>false</always_available>
        <category/>
        <fallback>false</fallback>
        <intent_ends_session>false</intent_ends_session>
        <keyword>WhatsHappeningOutages</keyword>
        <name>What's happening? (Outages)</name>
        <next_intent/>
        <order/>
        <output_speech_format/>
        <reprompt_speech_format/>
        <script><![CDATA[(function(content, attributes, erb){
	var introMessage = "Here is a list of today's outages: ";
	var outroMessage = '';
	var msg = '';
	
	var o = new GlideRecord('cmdb_ci_outage');
	o.addEncodedQuery('begin<javascript:gs.daysAgoStart(0)^endISEMPTY^typeINdegradation,outage');
	o.query();
	
	while (o.next()){		
		var updatedArr = o.begin.getDisplayValue().split(" ");
		var updatedDate = updatedArr[0];
		var updatedTime = updatedArr[1].split(":");
		updatedTime = updatedTime[0] + ":" + updatedTime[1];
		
		introMessage += "There is a " + o.type.getDisplayValue() + " affecting the " + o.cmdb_ci.getDisplayValue() + " business service. ";
		introMessage += "This " + o.type.getDisplayValue() + " started on " + updatedDate +  " at " + updatedTime + ". ";		
	}
	
	outroMessage += "To hear the list of outages again, say 'hear outages'. To go back to the status for today, say 'What's happening today'.";
	
	msg = "<speak>" + introMessage + outroMessage + "</speak>";
	
	erb.setOutputSpeech("SSML", "", msg);
	//erb.setReprompt("SSML", "", "<speak>" + outroMessage + "</speak>");
	erb.setEnd(false);
	
	result = erb.getResponse();
	
})(content, attributes, new EchoResponseBuilder());]]></script>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>package_private</access><active>true</active><api_name>x_snc_amazon_echo.EchoResponseBuilder</api_name><client_callable>false</client_callable><description/><name>EchoResponseBuilder</name><script><![CDATA[var EchoResponseBuilder = Class.create();
EchoResponseBuilder.prototype = {
	initialize: function() {
		this.response = {};
		this.response.response = {};
		this.response.version = '1;0';

	},

	setAttributes: function(attrObj) {
		this.response.sessionAttributes = attrObj;
		return;
	},

	setOutputSpeech: function(type, text, ssml){
		var o = {};
		o.type = type + '';
		o.text = text;
		o.ssml = ssml;

		this.response.response.outputSpeech = o;
		return;

	},

	setCard: function(type, title, content, text, imageObj){
		var c = {};
		c.type = type;
		c.text = text;
		c.content = content;
		c.image.smallImageUrl = imageObj.small;
		c.image.largeImageUrl = imageObj.large;

		this.response.response.card = c;
		return;

	},

	setReprompt: function(type, text, ssml){
		var r = {};
		r.outputSpeech = {};
		r.outputSpeech.ssml = ssml;
		r.outputSpeech.type = type;
		r.outputSpeech.text = text;

		this.response.response.reprompt = r;
		return;
	},

	setEnd: function(endSession){
		this.response.response.shouldEndSession = endSession + '';
	},

	getResponse: function() {
		return this.response;
	},

	type: 'EchoResponseBuilder'
};]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_include</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>jc</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2016-04-16 00:36:38</sys_created_on><sys_customer_update>true</sys_customer_update><sys_id>2227a5351372d200d0143d622244b0ae</sys_id><sys_mod_count>21</sys_mod_count><sys_name>EchoResponseBuilder</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Amazon Echo" source="x_snc_amazon_echo">101eb7da13a21200d0143d622244b063</sys_package><sys_policy>read</sys_policy><sys_replace_on_upgrade>false</sys_replace_on_upgrade><sys_scope display_value="Amazon Echo">101eb7da13a21200d0143d622244b063</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_include_2227a5351372d200d0143d622244b0ae</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>jc</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2017-04-13 20:58:08</sys_updated_on></sys_script_include></record_update>

<record_update table="x_snc_amazon_echo_intent">
    <x_snc_amazon_echo_intent action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE">
        <active>false</active>
        <always_available>false</always_available>
        <category/>
        <fallback>false</fallback>
        <intent_ends_session>false</intent_ends_session>
        <keyword>CheckStatusInc</keyword>
        <name>Check Status (Step 2)</name>
        <next_intent/>
        <order/>
        <output_speech_format/>
        <reprompt_speech_format/>
        <script><![CDATA[(function(content, attributes, erb){
	var num = "INC" + content.Number.value;
	
	var inc = new GlideRecord('incident');
	if (inc.get('number', num)){
		var updatedArr = inc.sys_updated_on.getDisplayValue().split(" ");
		var updatedDate = updatedArr[0];
		var updatedTime = updatedArr[1].split(":");
		updatedTime = updatedTime[0] + ":" + updatedTime[1];
		
		var notes = inc.comments.getJournalEntry(-1);
		var na = notes.split("\n\n");
		notes = na[0];
		
		//Message output...
		msg = "<speak>";
		msg += "The current status of your incident is: " + inc.state.getDisplayValue() + ". ";
		msg += "Your incident was last updated on: " + updatedDate + " at " + updatedTime  + ". ";
		
		if (notes != "" && notes != null) {
			notes = notes.split("\n");
			msg += "The last update was: " + notes[1] + ".";
		}
		
		msg += "</speak>";
		erb.setOutputSpeech("SSML", "", msg);
		//End message output
	} else {
		erb.setReprompt("PlainText", "I was unable to find that Incident. What was that Incident number again?");
	}
	erb.setEnd(true);
	
	result = erb.response;
})(content, attributes, new EchoResponseBuilder());]]></script>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_metadata_link"><sys_metadata_link action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><directory>update</directory><documentkey>a1727acadb5db200d1a9f1351d9619bb</documentkey><payload><?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<record_update table="x_snc_amazon_echo_intent">
    <x_snc_amazon_echo_intent action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE">
        <active>true</active>
        <always_available>false</always_available>
        <category/>
        <fallback>false</fallback>
        <intent_ends_session>false</intent_ends_session>
        <keyword>ThisWeeksChanges</keyword>
        <name>Are there any Changes this week?</name>
        <next_intent/>
        <order>400</order>
        <output_speech_format/>
        <reprompt_speech_format/>
        <script><![CDATA[(function(content, attributes, erb){
	//This returned an invalid SSML error. gotta check this...
	
	var introMessage = "Here is a list of Changes to be implemented this week: ";
	var outroMessage = '';
	var msg = '';
	var hasChanges = false;
	
	var chg = new GlideRecord('change_request');
	chg.addEncodedQuery('active=true^start_dateONThis week@javascript:gs.beginningOfThisWeek()@javascript:gs.endOfThisWeek()');
	chg.query();
	
	while (chg.next()){		
		var updatedArr = chg.end_date.getDisplayValue().split(" ");
		var updatedDate = updatedArr[0];
		var updatedTime = updatedArr[1].split(":");
		updatedTime = updatedTime[0] + ":" + updatedTime[1];
		
		var num = chg.number.toString();
		var numS = num.slice(-7);		
		
		var chgNum = "<say-as interpret-as='spell-out'>" + "CHG" + "</say-as> <say-as interpret-as='digits'>" + numS + "</say-as>";
		
		introMessage += "Change " + chgNum + " is a " + chg.type.getDisplayValue() + " Change affecting the " + chg.cmdb_ci.getDisplayValue() + " Configuration Item. ";
		introMessage += "The current risk value is: " + chg.risk.getDisplayValue() + ". ";
		introMessage += "The purpose of the change is: " + chg.short_description + ". ";
		introMessage += "This change is scheduled to end on " + updatedDate + " at " + updatedTime + ". ";
		hasChanges = true;
	}
	
	
	if (!hasChanges)
		introMessage = "There are no Changes scheduled to be implemented today. ";
	
	outroMessage += "To hear the list of Changes again, say 'This Weeks Changes'.";
	
	msg = "<speak>" + introMessage + outroMessage + "</speak>";
	
	erb.setOutputSpeech("SSML", "", msg);
	erb.setEnd(false);
	
	result = erb.getResponse();
	
})(content, attributes, new EchoResponseBuilder());]]></script>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_metadata_link"><sys_metadata_link action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><directory>unload</directory><documentkey>18ca4a53db0ef60015f2de01ce9619e8</documentkey><payload><?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<record_update table="x_snc_amazon_echo_intent">
    <x_snc_amazon_echo_intent action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE">
        <active>true</active>
        <always_available>true</always_available>
        <category/>
        <fallback>false</fallback>
        <intent_ends_session>false</intent_ends_session>
        <keyword>CriticalSecurityIncidents</keyword>
        <name>Hear Critical Security Incidents</name>
        <next_intent/>
        <order/>
        <output_speech_format>SSML</output_speech_format>
        <reprompt_speech_format/>
        <script><![CDATA[(function(current, content, attributes, ER, IntentUtils){
	var msg = '<speak>';

	var gr = new GlideRecord('sn_si_incident');
	gr.addEncodedQuery('active=true^priority=1');
	gr.query();

	while (gr.next()){
		msg += "Incident " + IntentUtils.taskNumberToSSML(gr);
		msg += (!gr.assigned_to ? " is unassigned " : (' is assigned to ' + gr.assigned_to.getDisplayValue() + ', '));
		var updatedDateTime = IntentUtils.formatDateTime(gr.sys_updated_on);

		msg += 'and was last updated on ' + updatedDateTime.date + ' at ' + updatedDateTime.time + '. ';

		msg += "The last update was: " + IntentUtils.getLastCommentOrWorkNote('comments', gr);
	}

	msg += "</speak>";

	ER.setOutputSpeech(current.output_speech_format, "", msg);
	ER.setEnd(current.intent_ends_session);
	result = ER.response; //Required
})(current, content, attributes, new EchoResponseBuilder(), new IntentUtils());]]></script>
        <slot_name_1/>
        <slot_name_2/>
        <slot_name_3/>
        <slot_type_1/>
        <slot_type_2/>
        <slot_type_3/>
        <sys_created_by>jc</sys_created_by>
        <sys_created_on>2017-04-16 04:34:46</sys_created_on>
        <sys_id>18ca4a53db0ef60015f2de01ce9619e8</sys_id>
        <sys_mod_count>15</sys_mod_count>
        <sys_updated_by>jc</sys_updated_by>
        <sys_updated_on>2017-04-16 05:18:51</sys_updated_on>
        <top_level_intent>false</top_level_intent>
    </x_snc_amazon_echo_intent>
</record_update>
